                           <p>The note is written in Amharic; it is dated by 1924 year of mercy (= 1931/32 A.D.) and mentions several individuals, among whom ras Gugsa, perhaps Gugsa ʾArʾaya (1882-1933).</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><locus target="#2rb">Fol. 2rb</locus>: </span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Record concerning reconciliation</span></span> (?).</span></span></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB" unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fol. 2rb: </span><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4768;&#4726;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4923;&#4853;&#4675;&#4757;&#4755;&#4961; &#4808;&#4845;&#4824;&#4654;&#4961; &#4768;&#4704;&#4651;&#4669;&#4961; &#4626;&#4851;&#4649;&#4961; &#4704;&#4632;&#4652;&#4725;&#4961; &#4720;&#4896;&#4621;&#4720;&#4813;&#4961; &#4768;&#4726;&#4961; &#4808;&#4616;&#4853;&#4637;&#4961; &#4709;&#4616;&#4813;&#4961; &#4781;&#4851;&#4811;&#4725;&#4961; &#4752;&#4704;&#4649;&#4961; &#4707;&#4669;&#4845;&#4961; &#4632;&#4853;&#4741;&#4757;&#4961; &#4773;&#4755;&#4961; &#4768;&#4726;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4923;&#4853;&#4675;&#4757;&#4961; &#4813;&#4752;&#4725;&#4961; &#4666;&#4670;&#4961; &#4632;&#4652;&#4725;&#4961; &#4725;&#4808;&#4616;&#4848;&#4616;&#4733;&#4961; &#4709;&#4616;&#4813;&#4961; &#4720;&#4936;&#4925;&#4632;&#4811;&#4621;&#4961; &#4704;&#4632;&#4637;&#4624;&#4653;&#4961; &#4709;&#4661;&#4651;&#4725;&#4961; &#4851;&#4765;&#4752;&#4725;&#4961; &#4704;&#4621;&#4817;&#4621;&#4961; &#4651;&#4661;&#4961; &#4873;&#4877;&#4659;&#4961;</span></span></span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;"> </span><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#8230;</span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is written in Amharic; it is dated by 1924 year of mercy (= 1931/32 A.D.) and mentions several individuals, among whom ras Gugsa, perhaps Gugsa ʾArʾaya (1882-1933).</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><locus target="#2rb">Fol. 2rb</locus>: Unclear note.</span></span></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span lang="AMH" unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fol. 2rb: </span><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4768;&#4632;&#4961;</span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> </span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4978;&#4961;</span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> </span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4616;&#4637;&#4843;&#4829;&#4843;&#4961;</span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> </span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4978;&#4987;&#4808;&#4977;&#4987;&#4981;&#4970;&#4961;</span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> </span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4768;&#4632;&#4720;&#4961;</span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> </span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4637;&#4613;&#4648;&#4725;&#4961;</span></span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> </span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&#8230;</span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is crudely written in Amharic in blue pen and is barely legible. It was written on 10 Miyazya 1942 year of mercy (= 5 April 1950 A.D.).</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><locus target="#8rb">Fol. 8rb</locus>: </span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Record concerning reconciliation</span></span> (?).</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fol. 8rb: </span><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4901;&#4677;&#4637;&#4722;&#4961; &#4974;&#4672;&#4757;&#4961; &#4981;&#4975;&#4819;&#4637;&#4961;</span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;"> </span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4773;&#4755;&#4961; &#4768;&#4726;&#4961; &#4808;&#4648;&#4656;&#4961; &#4709;&#4649;&#4961; &#4970;&#4755;&#4961; &#4808;</span></span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">[<span style="font-size: large;">&#4845;</span>]<span style="font-size: large;">&#4824;&#4654;&#4961; &#4720;&#4768;&#4637;&#4651;&#4725;&#4961; &#4709;&#4649;&#4961; &#4672;&#4653;&#4704;&#4813;&#4961;</span> </span><span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#8230;</span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is crudely written in strong purple ink in Amharic. It is dated by 6 Ṭǝqǝmt 1947 year of mercy (= 3 October 1954 A.D.).</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><locus target="#52ra">Fol. 52ra</locus>: </span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Record concerning reconciliation</span></span>.</span></span></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB" unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fol. 52ra: </span><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4840;&#4768;&#4648;&#4755;&#4961; &#4840;&#4920;&#4768;&#4848;&#4707;&#4961; &#4656;&#4707;&#4733;&#4961; &#4669;&#4635;&#4877;&#4620;&#4961; &#4851;&#4763;&#4728;&#4813;&#4961; &#4877;&#4651;&#4829;&#4635;&#4733;&#4961; &#4739;&#4845;&#4617;&#4961; &#4843;&#4726;&#4961; &#4608;&#4880;&#4661;&#4961; &#4773;&#4755;&#4961; &#4843;&#4726;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4645;&#4619;&#4660;&#4961; &#4611;&#4756;&#4723;&#4961; &#4768;&#4709;&#4653;&#4611;&#4961; &#4843;&#4726;&#4961; &#4778;&#4851;&#4753;&#4961; &#4773;&#4755;&#4961; &#4843;&#4726;&#4961; &#4656;&#4709;&#4630;&#4961; &#4667;&#4616;&#4675;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4632;&#4661;&#4672;&#4621;&#4961;</span></span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;"> </span><span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#8230;</span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is written in Amharic and mentions several individuals, e.g., grazmač Ḫaylu, ʾato Hagwäs, ʾato Gäbrä Śǝllase, ʾato Kidanu, šaläqa Gäbrä Mäsqäl and others.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><locus target="#52ra">Fol. 52ra</locus>-b: </span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Record concerning reconciliation</span></span>.</span></span></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB" unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fol. 52ra:</span><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;"> </span><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4977;&#4672;&#4757;&#4961; &#4877;&#4757;&#4710;&#4725;&#4961; &#4980;&#4977;&#4768;&#4632;&#4961; &#4776;&#4707;&#4669;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4770;&#4840;&#4657;&#4661;&#4961; &#4720;&#4619;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4629;</span></span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">[<span style="font-size: large;">&#4845;</span>]<span style="font-size: large;">&#4808;&#4725;&#4961; &#4736;&#4849;&#4873;&#4961; &#4752;&#4872;&#4648;&#4961; &#4941;&#4869;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4770;&#4840;</span>[<span style="font-size: large;">&#4657;&#4661;</span><span style="font-size: large;">&#4961;</span>] <span style="font-size: large;">&#4720;&#4619;&#4961;</span> </span><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#8230;</span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is crudely written in blue pen in Amharic. It is dated 9 Gǝnbot 1939 (= 4 May 1947 A.D.) and mentions several individuals, e.g., Gäbrä ʾIyäsus and Gäbrä Ḥǝw(y)ät.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a9"><p>&#160;<span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"><locus target="#148ra">Fol. 148ra</locus>: </span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Record concerning reconciliation</span></span>.</span></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB" unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fol. 148ra: </span><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4978;&#4987;&#4980;&#4970;&#4768;&#4632;&#4720;&#4961; &#4637;&#4613;&#4648;&#4725;&#4961; &#4635;&#4829;&#4843;&#4961; &#4970;&#4672;&#4757;&#4961; &#4632;&#4653;&#4840;&#4725;&#4961; &#4848;&#4621;&#4675;&#4961; &#4843;&#4707;&#4724;&#4961; &#4923;&#4853;&#4677;&#4961; &#4616;&#4720;&#4709;&#4653;&#4611;&#4757;&#4961; &#4720;&#4808;&#4621;&#4868;&#4961; &#4653;&#4661;&#4720;&#4845;&#4961; &#4808;&#4621;&#4868;&#4961; &#4704;&#4667;&#4845;&#4961; &#4720;&#4781;&#4616;&#4961; &#4611;&#4757;&#4661;&#4961; &#4720;&#4661;&#4939;&#4845;&#4961;</span></span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;"> </span><span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#8230;</span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is crudely written in Amharic and it is dated by 2 Miyazya 1932 year of mercy (= 28 March 1940 A.D.). It concludes with a fingerprint.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a10"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><locus target="#148v">Fol. 148v</locus>: List of guarantors (?).</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is written in Amharic and is partly illegible due to faded ink.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a11"><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><locus target="#149v">Fol. 149v</locus>: List of guarantors (?).</span></span><span lang="EN-GB" unicode="" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fol. 149b:</span><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;"> </span><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#4840;&#4709;&#4653;&#4664;&#4961; &#4811;&#4741;&#4661;&#4961; &#4757;&#4667;&#4845;&#4961; &#4632;&#4853;&#4741;&#4757;&#4961; &#4797;&#4616;&#4724;&#4961; &#4720;&#4896;&#4616;&#4621;&#4941;&#4811;&#4621;&#4961; &#4840;&#4632;&#4648;&#4659;&#4961; &#4811;&#4661;&#4961; &#4851;&#4661;&#4843;&#4961; &#4819;&#4845;&#4756;&#4962; &#4840;&#4808;</span></span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">[<span style="font-size: large;">&#4757;</span>]<span style="font-size: large;">&#4853;&#4633;&#4961; &#4840;&#4624;&#4878;&#4661;&#4961; &#4811;&#4661;&#4961; &#4632;&#4648;&#4659;&#4961; &#4840;&#4720;&#4661;&#4939;&#4845;&#4961; &#4811;&#4661;&#4961; &#4768;&#4726;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4629;&#4845;&#4808;&#4725;&#4962; &#4840;&#4648;&#4851;&#4961; &#4811;&#4661;&#4961; &#4709;&#4649;&#4961; &#4720;&#4661;&#4939;&#4845;&#4962; &#4840;&#4768;&#4726;&#4961; &#4851;&#4661;&#4723;&#4961;</span> </span><span lang="EN-GB" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala;">&#8230;</span></span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is written in red ink in Amharic and lists a number of guarantors for several individuals.</p>
                        </item>
